The paper deals with string pattern matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The focus of the paper is on a variant of string pattern matching on multi-track strings, which are a generalization of strings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) categories. Additionally, the paper presents a reduction from multi-track strings to single-track strings, which involves manipulating the structure of the input. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
